---
description: Require rtk wrapper for all terminal commands
alwaysApply: true
---

## Terminal commands

Before running any shell command, check whether `rtk` supports it. If yes, use `rtk` — no exceptions.

```bash
# Wrong
git status
pnpm test
gh pr list

# Correct
rtk git status
rtk pnpm test
rtk gh pr list
```

## Banned patterns

| Raw command | Use instead |
|-------------|-------------|
| `git ...` | `rtk git ...` |
| `gh ...` | `rtk gh ...` |
| `pnpm ...` | `rtk pnpm ...` |
| `npm ...` | `rtk pnpm ...` |

## Self-check

Before every bash call: "Am I about to type a raw CLI command? STOP. Use rtk."

## Fallback

Use raw commands only when `rtk` does not support the needed behavior. When unsure, try `rtk` first.

Structured file tools (`Read`, `Grep`, `Glob`) do not go through `rtk`.
